    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Creeping, mat-forming pioneer species found low on foreshore dunes. The large, slightly-succulent leaves may be paddle-shaped or deeply lobed and are covered with white felt. The flowers are borne on short, wooly, curving stems and often overtopped by the large leaves. The narrow outer petals are bright yellow and often well-spaced and the central flowers a more greenish yellow.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_9354",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Plants up to about 200 mm tall, 2 m or more across, leaves about 50-60 mm long and 50 mm wide and flowers about 30 mm across.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_9355",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to southern Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> About Hondeklip Bay on the west coast to Mozambique.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_9356",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Common pioneer species found low on coastal dunes, where can extend almost down to high water mark. Performs important function in dune stabilisation and often creates hummocks on the sand. Flowers pollinated by a variety of bees and flies. Seeds dispersed by wind and remain viable in both salt and freshwater, so can be widely dispersed by ocean currents<i>.</i></p><p>Has been introduced to Australia, where it is now a common weed of coastal areas.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_9357",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_9358",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Flowers throughout the year.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_9359",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>Fairly distinctive in both habitat and appearance.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_9360",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        }
    ],
